An analysis of variance (ANOVA) was performed using statistical software (SPSS version 15.0, SPSS Inc., Chicago, IL). The ANOVA test is used to investigate whether significant differences in mean values exist between two or more groups. In this study, we want to investigate what the effect of temperature on the one hand, and the effect of doxorubicin concentration on the other hand, is on cell survival. Using a general linear model, the viability is statistically modeled as:
